    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Ad on Gold Medal Precedes Coverage</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Alysia Dashef letter criticizes NBC for running advertisement congratulating Stacy Dragila for gold medal directly before beginning of their coverage of her gold medal effort in pole vault</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Apparently the folks at NBC have not paid attention to the widespread disdain of their coverage of the Olympic Games. Amazingly, NBC ran a Visa advertisement congratulating Stacy Dragila for a gold medal directly before beginning their coverage of her gold medal effort in the pole vault.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Apparently the folks at NBC have not paid attention to the widespread disdain of their coverage of the Olympic Games. Amazingly, NBC ran a Visa advertisement congratulating Stacy Dragila for a gold medal directly before beginning their coverage of her gold medal effort in the pole vault.</p>
        <p>Whether stupidity or greed, ultimately NBC loses as viewers across America flip to any number of other channels for more entertaining fare.</p>
        <p>ALYSIA DASHEF  New York</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
